ular given name, of Continental Germanic origin, from <i>haim</i> ‘home’ + <i>rīc</i> ‘power, ruler’. It was an Old French name, adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to Britain. It has been borne by eight kings of England. Not until the 17th century did the form <i>Henry</i> (as opposed to   Harry  ) become the standard vernacular form, mainly under the influence of the Latin form <i>Henricus</i> and French <i>Henri</i>."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1356696,"age":26,"year":"1506","julianDay":2271115,"description":"The Netherlands is inherited by the future Habsburg Emperor and King of Spain Charles V.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1356697,"age":36,"year":"1516","julianDay":2274767,"description":"The Catholic King Charles I of Spain ruled the Netherlands.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1356698,"age":92,"year":"1572","julianDay":2295221,"description":"William of Orange was recognized as viceroy of Holland, Friesland and Utrecht.","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"When Maria Adriaen Henric Eements Heems was born from 1480 to 1481, in Netherlands, her father, Adriaen Hendricks Eements, was 31 and her mother, Maria Jansen, was 31. She had at least 1 daughter with Jan Willems Vanden Breemden."},"et":{"1480–1481–":"1480 kuni 1481–Surnud","1480–Female":"1480–Surnud","1475–Male":"1475–Surnud","1500–1560":"1500–1560","1450–1501":"1450–1501","1450–Female":"1450–Surnud","1501":"1501","1500":"1500","1475":"1475","1572":"1572","1450":"1450","1560":"1560","1480–1481":"1480 kuni 1481","1480":"1480","1506":"1506","1516":"1516","Netherlands":"Madalmaad","Breda, Breda, Noord-Brabant, Pays-Bas":"Breda, Noord-Brabant, Madalmaad"},"fi":{"1480–1481–":"vuodesta 1480 vuoteen 1481–Kuollut","1480–Female":"1480–Kuollut","1475–Male":"1475–Kuollut","1500–1560":"1500–1560","1450–1501":"1450–1501","1450–Female":"1450–Kuollut","1501":"1501","1500":"1500","1475":"1475","1572":"1572","1450":"1450","1560":"1560","1480–1481":"vuodesta 1480 vuoteen 1481","1480":"1480","1506":"1506","1516":